Sentencas: The mixed ionic-electronic conductor La2NiO4+delta was investigated as potential cathode material for protonic conducting solid oxide fuel cells (PC-SOFCs) based on La5.5WO11.25-delta electrolyte.
Titulo: Study of Pr and Pr and Co doped La2NiO4+δ as cathodes for La5.5WO11.25-δ based protonic conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: Firstly the chemical compatibility between cathode and electrolyte phases (La2NiO4+delta and La5.5WO11.25-delta respectively) was studied.
Titulo: Study of Pr and Pr and Co doped La2NiO4+δ as cathodes for La5.5WO11.25-δ based protonic conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: Then, the electrochemical properties of this cathode were improved by partially substituting La and/or Ni, specifically La1.5Pr0.5NiO4+delta and La(1.5)Pro(0.5)Nio(0.8)Co(0.2)O(4+delta) were considered.
Titulo: Study of Pr and Pr and Co doped La2NiO4+δ as cathodes for La5.5WO11.25-δ based protonic conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: These two doped materials showed improved electrical conductivity and reduced polarization resistance, when tested as cathode in symmetrical cells.
Titulo: Study of Pr and Pr and Co doped La2NiO4+δ as cathodes for La5.5WO11.25-δ based protonic conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: In a second step, the microstructure of La(1.5)Pro(0.5)Nio(0.8)Co(0.2)O(4+delta) was optimized by varying the firing temperature of the cathode.
Titulo: Study of Pr and Pr and Co doped La2NiO4+δ as cathodes for La5.5WO11.25-δ based protonic conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: The performance of these mixed conductors is limited by medium frequencies associated processes while they show lower polarization resistances (Rp) than conventional composites based on La5.5WO11.25-delta and pure electronic conductors.
Titulo: Study of Pr and Pr and Co doped La2NiO4+δ as cathodes for La5.5WO11.25-δ based protonic conducting fuel cells

Sentencas: La(1.5)Pro(0.5)Nio(0.8)Co(0.2)O(4+delta) cathode sintered at 1050 degrees C exhibits the best electrochemical performance on a La5.5WO11.25-delta-based PC-SOFC, achieving Rp = 0.62 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C in wet air.
Titulo: Study of Pr and Pr and Co doped La2NiO4+δ as cathodes for La5.5WO11.25-δ based protonic conducting fuel cells
